# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
# |<----   Using a Maximum Of 100 Characters   ---->|

# Explain why this change is being made
# |<----   Try To Limit Each Line to a Maximum Of 72 Characters   ---->|

# Provide links or keys to any relevant tickets, articles or other resources
# Example: BREAKING CHANGE: <description>
# Example: Closes #123
# Example: Ref #456

# --- COMMIT END ---
# Type can be
#    feat     (new feature)
#    fix      (bug fix)
#    refactor (refactoring production code)
#    style    (formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change)
#    docs     (changes to documentation)
#    test     (adding or refactoring tests; no production code change)
#    chore    (updating build tasks, package manager configs, etc; no production code change)
#    perf     (performance improvement)
#    build    (build system or dependencies)
#    ci       (CI/CD configuration)
#    revert   (revert a previous commit)
# --------------------
# Scope is optional and should be the module or component affected
# Examples: kernel, adapter, web, persistence, etc.
# --------------------
# Remember to:
#   1. Capitalize the subject line
#   2. Use the imperative mood in the subject line
#   3. Do not end the subject line with a period
#   4. Separate subject from body with a blank line
#   5. Use the body to explain what and why vs. how
#   6. Can use multiple lines with "-" for bullet points in body
# --------------------
